Tri-Chol by Biotics Research supplies a unique combination of botanical components with specific micronutrients, with the focus on inositol hexaniacinate, to help maintain cholesterol levels that are already within a normal range.

Active Ingredients:
Asian Water Plantain, Bitter Orange, Choline, Chromium, Commiphora Mukul, Fo-Ti, Guggul, Guggul, Inositol Hexaniacinate, Niacin, Polygonum Cuspidatum, Polygonum Multiflorum

Tri-Chol™ supplies a unique combination of botanical components with specific micronutrients, including inositol hexaniacinate, as a support for modulating cholesterol levels.  

Features

  • Nutrients Combined to Support Healthy Blood Lipid Levels, Healthy Cholesterol, Sterols, Polygonum, Niacin, Chromium, Resveratrol
  • PROMOTES HEALTHY CHOLESTEROL LEVELS: Tri-Chol contains a blend of nutrients such as chromium, niacin and choline along with botanical support for healthy lipid metabolism. A mixture of phenols and phenol derivatives, Tri-Chol includes Bitter Orange, Polygonum cuspidatum and Asian Water Plantain.
  • SAFE FORM OF NIACIN: Tri-Chol uses one of the safest forms of Niacin, inositol hexaniacinate, which has long been used in Europe.
  • PROVIDES ANTIOXIDANT PROTECTION: The botanicals in Tri-Chol have strong antioxidant properties, helping mitigate oxidative damage in the body.
